WEBVTT

00:04.404 --> 00:05.372 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.405 --> 00:07.173 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.207 --> 00:11.444 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: In a
stunning move,
the White House announces
President Trump

00:11.478 --> 00:14.581 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has fired FBI Director James
Comey.

00:14.614 --> 00:20.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Plus, I sit down with Maine
Senator Susan
Collins to talk about the Comey
firing and

00:20.387 --> 00:25.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the fate of the Republicans'
health care bill
as it makes its way to her side
of Capitol

00:25.358 --> 00:27.127 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Hill.

00:27.160 --> 00:32.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And searching for hope in Havana
-- why some
lung cancer patients are making
the trek to

00:32.465 --> 00:34.467 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Cuba for a promising medication.

00:34.501 --> 00:35.769 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

00:35.802 --> 00:37.771 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIMOTHY GOGGINS, Oncologist: I'm
surprised
Mick's still here.

00:37.804 --> 00:42.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I do believe that, outside
of divine intervention,
there's some sort of scientific
basis to what

00:43.009 --> 00:44.244 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he's doing.

00:44.277 --> 00:51.551 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:51.584 --> 00:54.487 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:54.521 --> 01:03.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Our lead story is
breaking
right this minute.

01:03.630 --> 01:07.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump has fired James
Comey as the
director of the FBI.

01:07.700 --> 01:12.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
White House Press Secretary Sean
Spicer made
the announcement just moments
ago.

01:12.672 --> 01:16.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And here to tell us what we know
at this time
is our own White House
correspondent John

01:16.876 --> 01:17.844 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yang.

01:17.877 --> 01:19.412 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
John, this looks like a bolt out
of the blue.

01:19.446 --> 01:20.413 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What have you learned?

01:20.447 --> 01:22.215 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: It was absolutely out
of the blue.

01:22.248 --> 01:25.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was after we were told, the
White House
press were told there would be
no more news

01:25.385 --> 01:27.287 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
developments for the night.

01:27.320 --> 01:32.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sean Spicer walked into the
Briefing Room,
read a very brief statement
saying that President

01:32.258 --> 01:38.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trump had fired James Comey on
the recommendation
of the attorney general, Jeff
Sessions, and

01:38.798 --> 01:43.603 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the deputy attorney general, Rod
Rosenstein.

01:43.636 --> 01:45.472 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We're getting letters.

01:45.505 --> 01:51.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're slowly getting bits and
pieces of the
reasons why, the letters that
Sessions sent

01:51.277 --> 01:57.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the president recommending
this move and
Rosenstein's memo recommending
it as well.

01:57.450 --> 02:03.323 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It appears to center around
Comey's handling
of the investigation into
Hillary Clinton's

02:03.356 --> 02:11.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
e-mails, ironically enough, that
his announcement,
his holding a press conference
in July clearing

02:11.164 --> 02:15.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
her, but also criticizing her at
the same
time.

02:15.335 --> 02:17.871 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Usually, they don't make
statements like that.

02:17.904 --> 02:22.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Usually, they just say the
investigation is
closed, no charges have been
brought.

02:22.408 --> 02:27.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rosenstein said his memo that
Comey -- that
-- I'm sorry -- he, Rosenstein,
doesn't understood

02:27.680 --> 02:34.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Comey's refusal to accept --
quote -- "nearly
universal judgment that he was
mistaken in

02:34.854 --> 02:36.756 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that."

02:36.789 --> 02:40.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, mistaken in
not going ahead
and prosecuting Hillary Clinton
for what happened

02:40.894 --> 02:42.662 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with her e-mails?

02:42.695 --> 02:47.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: As I understand it,
mistaken in
going public with what they had
gathered and

02:47.634 --> 02:52.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
then saying we're not going the
prosecute,
rather than just saying, we're
closing this

02:52.605 --> 02:54.741 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
investigation with no
prosecution.

02:54.774 --> 02:59.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: John, did we know
that this
kind of an investigation was
under way at

02:59.546 --> 03:04.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Justice Department looking
into Comey's
handling of the Clinton e-mail
matter?

03:04.217 --> 03:07.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The irony of this is
that all this
criticism had been coming from
the Democrats,

03:07.921 --> 03:13.226 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but apparently this was being
looked at within
the Justice Department.

03:13.259 --> 03:18.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now, this is also an FBI
director who was
conducting an investigation into
possible

03:18.798 --> 03:22.335 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ties between the president's
campaign and
Russia.

03:22.368 --> 03:25.872 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There will be, I'm sure,
conspiracy theorists.

03:25.905 --> 03:30.443 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I'm sure there will be
allegations of, were
they looking for a reason to do
this?

03:30.476 --> 03:35.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And up until now,
President
Trump has given every indication
that he wanted

03:35.081 --> 03:36.883 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
James Comey to continue.

03:36.916 --> 03:41.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Although today, very
telling, perhaps
tellingly, we don't know, there
was -- after

03:41.221 --> 03:47.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the letter was sent, he had to
correct, clean
up some of his testimony to the
Senate regarding

03:47.694 --> 03:51.764 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- again regarding this e-mail
investigation,
a separate instance.

03:51.798 --> 03:59.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sean Spicer was asked, does the
president
-- still have the support of the
president?

03:59.138 --> 04:02.442 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sean said: I have not spoken to
the president
since this development.

04:02.475 --> 04:06.279 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would be reluctant to say that
now without
speaking to the president first.

04:06.312 --> 04:09.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, John Yang,
again, this
story breaking just as we're
sitting here

04:09.215 --> 04:10.917 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this evening.

04:10.950 --> 04:13.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It broke just 15 minutes before
we went on
the air at 6:00 Eastern,
learning that the

04:13.586 --> 04:18.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- from the White House, the
president has
fired the FBI director, James
Comey.

04:18.758 --> 04:23.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the issue you're talking
about right now,
John, has to do with what James
Comey said

04:24.030 --> 04:30.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
last month when he testified
before a Senate
hearing and, in essence, he
talked about how

04:30.770 --> 04:34.107 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he had handled the Clinton
e-mail matter.

04:34.140 --> 04:39.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And there had been
questions all
along in this process about
whether or not

04:39.712 --> 04:42.348 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Comey still had the support of
the president.

04:42.382 --> 04:44.250 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

04:44.284 --> 04:48.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And the question was
asked again
today, and Sean Spicer didn't
give the support.

04:48.488 --> 04:55.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, there is one interesting
line in the
president's letter to Comey
firing him.

04:55.561 --> 05:01.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said: "While I greatly
appreciate you informing
me on three separate
investigations that I

05:01.200 --> 05:06.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
am not under investigation, I
nevertheless
concur with the judgment of the
Department

05:06.606 --> 05:10.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Justice that you are not able
to effectively
lead the bureau."

05:10.276 --> 05:13.379 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All right, John
Yang, I want
you to stay with us.

05:13.413 --> 05:19.018 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the phone joining us now is
someone who
was a huge figure in the
Watergate investigation

05:19.052 --> 05:26.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
back in the early 1970s, which,
of course,
led to the resignation of
then-President Richard

05:26.092 --> 05:27.060 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Nixon.

05:27.093 --> 05:28.761 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're joined on the phone by
John Dean.

05:28.795 --> 05:32.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was the White House counsel
then for President
Nixon.

05:32.465 --> 05:34.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
John Dean, you're listening to
this.

05:34.267 --> 05:35.768 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What do you make of it?

05:35.802 --> 05:38.871 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN DEAN, Former White House
Counsel: Well,
it's not totally surprising.

05:38.905 --> 05:43.309 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I was actually brooding about it
at lunch
and wondering how Comey was
going to deal

05:43.343 --> 05:46.479 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with the screw-up on his
testimony.

05:46.512 --> 05:53.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I thought, for the sake of
the bureau,
he might step down, because he's
really splashed

05:53.553 --> 05:55.822 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
mud all over themselves with
this one.

05:55.855 --> 05:58.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Why did you think
this might
be so serious?

05:58.925 --> 06:05.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What was it about the mistake
which he made
in that testimony last month
that had you

06:05.198 --> 06:07.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
questioning?

06:07.066 --> 06:13.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DEAN: Well, his rationale
for how he
handled the Clinton
investigation vs. vis-a-vis

06:13.106 --> 06:19.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Trump investigation, where
he disclosed
one publicly and didn't disclose
the other,

06:19.379 --> 06:26.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is -- the rationale has been so
thin, and
the differences are really so
inconsequential,

06:26.853 --> 06:31.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that it made most -- really no
sense to what
he was saying.

06:31.090 --> 06:37.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, now when he gets up and
bolsters his case
with bogus evidence, he looks
really bad.

06:37.430 --> 06:43.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he doesn't look like a
director with an
even hand should look.

06:43.102 --> 06:50.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I don't know what Sessions
-- I didn't
hear anything about what
Sessions' position

06:50.543 --> 06:52.812 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was, but I thought he was in
trouble.

06:52.845 --> 06:56.048 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, that was just in the air
to me.

06:56.082 --> 07:00.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I was going to
read just briefly
from a portion of the letter
that was just

07:00.920 --> 07:04.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
issued by the White House, by
the attorney
general, Jeff Sessions.

07:04.257 --> 07:08.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says: "I have concluded a
fresh start is
needed at the leadership of the
FBI.

07:08.327 --> 07:13.299 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's essential this Department
of Justice
clearly reaffirm its commitment
to longstanding

07:13.332 --> 07:19.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
principles that ensure the
integrity and fairness
of federal investigations and
prosecutions."

07:19.172 --> 07:27.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're clearly trying to
connect their concern
about James Comey with the way
the Justice

07:27.046 --> 07:30.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Department operates and the
confidence the
American people and, of course,
the president

07:30.550 --> 07:32.318 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
have to have in that.

07:32.351 --> 07:34.821 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOHN DEAN: Absolutely true.

07:34.854 --> 07:36.789 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know, it's going to be very
difficult.

07:36.823 --> 07:42.762 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's not unlike post-Watergate,
when they
had a very difficult time
deciding who to

07:42.795 --> 07:48.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
select, and we had a series of
federal judges
who were put in there who were
absolutely

07:48.534 --> 07:50.937 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
beyond any kind of question.

07:50.970 --> 07:56.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Bill Webster was put in that
post, if you
recall, a former sitting federal
district

07:56.476 --> 08:03.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
court judge who had been a U.S.
attorney in
Saint Louis, and followed by
William Sessions,

08:03.316 --> 08:04.517 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
who got fired.

08:04.550 --> 08:05.518 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

08:05.551 --> 08:07.320 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Exactly.

08:07.353 --> 08:10.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, John Dean -- we're on the
phone with
John Dean, who, of course, was
the White House

08:10.089 --> 08:13.759 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
counsel to Richard Nixon.

08:13.793 --> 08:17.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are going to be a number
of comparisons
drawn out of this, one of them,
of course,

08:17.763 --> 08:25.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Saturday night -- so-called
Saturday night
massacre, when President Nixon
fired his attorney

08:25.771 --> 08:30.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
general and others because they
wouldn't carry
out his wishes in the time of
Watergate.

08:30.309 --> 08:33.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Any connection with that, or is
this a completely
different set of circumstances?

08:33.379 --> 08:35.948 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN DEAN: I think this is
different, Judy.

08:35.982 --> 08:39.619 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think it doesn't have any of
that kind of
feel.

08:39.652 --> 08:46.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Archibald Cox was defying the
president and
taking his own course of action
and taking

08:46.259 --> 08:50.296 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a -- making a decision that was
very much
placing Nixon in jeopardy.

08:50.329 --> 08:53.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I don't think we have any
similarities
here.

08:53.933 --> 08:59.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And just refresh
our memory
on the role of the FBI director.

08:59.438 --> 09:03.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is intended to be an
independent position,
is it not?

09:03.509 --> 09:09.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm asking to remind everyone
that the FBI
is conducting a critical
investigation right

09:09.248 --> 09:16.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
now into any connections between
the Trump
campaign for president and
Russian officials.

09:16.188 --> 09:23.262 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN DEAN: Well, it was
post-Watergate that
they -- indeed, after Hoover,
that the Congress

09:23.296 --> 09:29.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
made this a 10-year appointment,
to give it
some independence, where it
could go over

09:29.235 --> 09:32.305 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
from one president to the next.

09:32.338 --> 09:38.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The presidents do have the
ability, if they
don't have confidence in the
director, to

09:38.244 --> 09:42.815 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fire him, but we have not seen
that very often.

09:42.848 --> 09:45.718 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It has been the exception to the
rule.

09:45.751 --> 09:51.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have tried to depoliticize
the bureau,
which is the way it should be,
where we have

09:51.891 --> 10:00.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a politics-free federal
investigation unit,
but he is subject to the --
reports to the

10:00.333 --> 10:04.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
attorney general, who, of
course, is a political
appointee.

10:04.036 --> 10:07.340 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, there is always that filter.

10:07.373 --> 10:12.912 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But yet just the weight of the
bureau itself
carries its own independence.

10:12.945 --> 10:17.083 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And when it has strong
leadership, it is highly
respected.

10:17.116 --> 10:22.788 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When that leadership has not
been so strong,
it has been suspect.

10:22.822 --> 10:24.624 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we -- you're absolutely
right.

10:24.657 --> 10:30.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It couldn't come at a more
difficult time,
given the implications of the
Russian hacking

10:30.896 --> 10:32.898 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and how that's going to all
unravel.

10:32.932 --> 10:38.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And just quickly,
to wrap up,
John Dean, your sense of what
has happened

10:38.838 --> 10:45.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
here, you were saying at the
outset, didn't
surprise you that much, given
the mistake,

10:45.611 --> 10:50.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mistake in testimony that it
turns out James
Comey gave to the Congress last
month.

10:50.483 --> 10:57.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DEAN: Well, that certainly
gave both
-- because of the delay in
correcting it,

10:57.590 --> 11:02.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you immediately knew there was a
problem,
because Republicans had leaped
on it, they

11:02.094 --> 11:06.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were using it for political
purposes on bogus
information, so it was going the
embarrass

