cooperation, but, in many ways,
his approach,

43:27.972 --> 43:32.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which emphasizes economic
relations, fits
in with China's approach.

43:32.142 --> 43:35.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there may be more room to
cooperate than
we might think right now.

43:35.879 --> 43:37.615 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And one other
thing.

43:37.648 --> 43:41.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There has been some back and
forth between
the U.S. and South Korea
recently over this

43:41.251 --> 43:46.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
missile defense system called
THAAD, the acronym.

43:46.457 --> 43:47.591 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What has he said about that?

43:47.625 --> 43:49.460 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do you expect to happen
there?

43:49.493 --> 43:54.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID KANG: You know, the U.S.
missile defense
system THAAD, I think in some
ways has gotten

43:54.798 --> 43:58.569 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
blown up over the last year as a
bigger issue
than it really is.

43:58.602 --> 44:03.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China doesn't like it, but for
the last -- it
was announced last summer, so
we're coming

44:03.641 --> 44:09.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
up on an entire year that THAAD
has been in
deployment and is now fully
deployed.

44:09.146 --> 44:14.051 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But China and the United States
had been negotiating
with an empty chair in South
Korea because

44:14.084 --> 44:17.021 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the political power vacuum of
the previous
president.

44:17.054 --> 44:22.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So Moon has a lot on his plate,
but with the
proper diplomacy, I think he can
assuage some

44:22.526 --> 44:26.497 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of China's fears, while still
retaining the
missile defense system.

44:26.530 --> 44:30.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's his task as a president,
is to be able
to deal with both of these big
countries at

44:30.167 --> 44:31.935 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the same time.

44:31.969 --> 44:35.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Professor David
Kang at the
University of Southern
California, we thank

44:35.372 --> 44:36.674 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you.

44:36.707 --> 44:42.046 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DAVID KANG: My pleasure.

44:42.079 --> 44:43.881 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
cancer

44:43.914 --> 44:51.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now: a promising
lung cancer
treatment from Cuba that's
drawing attention

44:51.522 --> 44:53.624 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from U.S. patients.

44:53.657 --> 44:57.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some Americans are already
traveling there
to try the drug, in the hopes of
stopping

44:58.028 --> 44:59.830 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their cancer from growing.

44:59.863 --> 45:04.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Former President Obama cleared
the way for
collaboration between both
countries on such

45:04.735 --> 45:07.271 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
research, and clinical trials
have started.

45:07.304 --> 45:09.073 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Those trials may take years.

45:09.106 --> 45:14.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But early results have some
researchers intrigued
by this new form of
immunotherapy.

45:14.845 --> 45:18.215 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Special correspondent Amy
Guttman has the
story.

45:18.248 --> 45:23.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: Mick Phillips
travels from his
home near Green Bay, Wisconsin,
to Cuba once

45:23.587 --> 45:24.988 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a year.

45:25.022 --> 45:28.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Despite his passion for vintage
cars, that's
not what draws him.

45:28.992 --> 45:34.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He goes there for CimaVax, a
Cuban-made drug
used to treat cancer that's kept
him alive

45:34.164 --> 45:35.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
longer than any doctor
predicted.

45:35.999 --> 45:41.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICK PHILLIPS, Cancer Patient:
So, I have
this little lunch box here
that's insulated.

45:41.572 --> 45:49.079 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, in there, I carry my
medication and I
also carry gel packs.

45:49.113 --> 45:53.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: Phillips is 69
years old and
owns an industrial pump factory,
where he

45:53.350 --> 45:55.352 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
continues to work every day.

45:55.385 --> 46:00.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was first diagnosed with
non-small cell
lung cancer seven years ago.

46:00.424 --> 46:05.028 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After chemotherapy and radiation
treatment,
his cancer went into remission.

46:05.062 --> 46:08.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it returned less than a year
later, in
2011.

46:08.799 --> 46:14.505 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He did another round of
chemotherapy, then
took CimaVax, and is now in
remission.

46:14.538 --> 46:20.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Fewer than 5 percent of stage 4
lung cancer
patients like Phillips survive
for five years.

46:20.110 --> 46:24.014 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But CimaVax appears to be
improving those
odds for some.

46:24.047 --> 46:29.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICK PHILLIPS: I started the
CimaVax and have
been cancer-free ever since
then.

46:29.386 --> 46:33.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: And how long were
you supposed
to live once you went into
remission?

46:33.657 --> 46:36.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK PHILLIPS: The prognosis was
maybe six
months to a year.

46:36.627 --> 46:38.095 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: How many years ago
was that?

46:38.128 --> 46:39.997 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICK PHILLIPS: That was six
years ago.

46:40.030 --> 46:45.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: At La Pradera, a
hotel-like hospital
near Havana, Phillips pays about
$5,000 for

46:45.702 --> 46:47.905 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
an annual supply of CimaVax.

46:47.938 --> 46:51.208 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The doctor visit costs only $50.

46:51.241 --> 46:56.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in Wisconsin, Phillips says
he's lucky
that his oncologist, Dr. Timothy
Goggins,

46:56.814 --> 46:58.715 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
continues to treat him.

46:58.749 --> 47:02.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
American doctors can't prescribe
CimaVax,
because the Food and Drug
Administration won't

47:02.820 --> 47:06.323 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
approve it until U.S. clinical
trials can
prove its effectiveness.

47:06.356 --> 47:07.424 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

47:07.457 --> 47:08.425 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIMOTHY GOGGINS, Oncologist: How
are things
going?

47:08.458 --> 47:09.760 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICK PHILLIPS: Oh, pretty good.

47:09.793 --> 47:13.230 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
AMY GUTTMAN: Dr. Goggins
monitors Phillips
with regular scans.

47:13.263 --> 47:14.932 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

47:14.965 --> 47:18.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIMOTHY GOGGINS: Compare this to
where he
is today, no evidence of growth
necessarily

47:18.068 --> 47:19.036 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in that area.

47:19.069 --> 47:20.771 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In fact, there might even be
shrinkage.

47:20.804 --> 47:24.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would have expected, in this
case, further
growth, definitely within the
lungs.

47:24.641 --> 47:26.710 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm surprised Mick's still here.

47:26.743 --> 47:32.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I do believe that, outside
of divine intervention,
there's some sort of scientific
basis to what

47:32.349 --> 47:34.117 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he's doing.

47:34.151 --> 47:37.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: Published results
of trials done
in Cuba show those given CimaVax
lived, on

47:37.387 --> 47:42.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
average, as little as three
months and as
much as 11 months longer than
those not given

47:42.759 --> 47:44.094 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the drug.

47:44.127 --> 47:45.896 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Some did even better.

47:45.929 --> 47:50.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dr. Michael Caligiuri, president
of the American
Association for Cancer Research
says, even

47:50.868 --> 47:53.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with the success in Cuba, there
must be further
study.

47:53.937 --> 47:55.873 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

47:55.906 --> 47:57.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL CALIGIURI, President,
American Association
for Cancer Research: Whenever
there's an early

47:57.708 --> 48:02.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
evidence of efficacy in a single
population,
a single institution study, the
chance that

48:02.045 --> 48:08.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
it will be replicated
inter-institutionally
is real, but not a given.

48:08.085 --> 48:12.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: This facility
outside Havana
produces CimaVax.

48:12.089 --> 48:13.991 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It doesn't kill cancer cells.

48:14.024 --> 48:19.997 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Instead, it engages the
patient's immune system
to reduce the protein cancer
thrives on.

48:20.030 --> 48:26.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What makes this different from
other immunotherapies
is, it uses a patient's own
antibodies, rather

48:26.169 --> 48:31.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than manufactured ones, which
carries fewer
side effects and is cheaper.

48:31.375 --> 48:35.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Researchers at Roswell Park
Cancer Institute
in Buffalo, New York, waited
four years to

48:35.846 --> 48:40.851 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
get the green light for clinical
trials of
CimaVax that began in January.

48:40.884 --> 48:46.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The institute's chair of
immunology, Dr. Kelvin
Lee, was in Havana recently for
a conference.

48:46.189 --> 48:47.958 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

48:47.991 --> 48:50.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KELVIN LEE, Roswell Park Cancer
Institute:
In many cases, the tumors just
stop growing.

48:50.494 --> 48:52.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're there, but they don't
get any bigger.

48:52.663 --> 48:57.868 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The patient has the possibility
of going on
for a very long time.

48:57.901 --> 49:02.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: CimaVax is given by
injection
and is considered a therapeutic
drug for now.

49:02.773 --> 49:08.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Dr. Lee and his colleagues
are applying
for funding to test it as a
preventive vaccine

49:08.211 --> 49:09.780 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for high-risk patients.

49:09.813 --> 49:11.715 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

49:11.748 --> 49:15.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KELVIN LEE: Because it is safe,
inexpensive,
easy to administer, you could
use it, potentially,

49:15.352 --> 49:17.120 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to prevent lung cancer.

49:17.154 --> 49:21.224 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: The embargo that
prevented Cuba's
access to American
pharmaceuticals led the

49:21.258 --> 49:27.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
late President Fidel Castro to
invest heavily
in developing medicines and
vaccines.

49:27.731 --> 49:30.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Former President Obama traveled
to Cuba last
year.

49:30.600 --> 49:35.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He later announced new policies
making it
easier for American researchers
to apply for

49:35.872 --> 49:43.046 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FDA approval to trial Cuban
drugs in the United
States.

49:43.080 --> 49:47.751 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Mick Phillips voted for
President Trump, but
Mr. Trump has vowed to rollback
some of Obama's

49:47.784 --> 49:50.988 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
policies when it comes to Cuba
relations.

49:51.021 --> 49:52.756 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Phillips fears what that could
mean.

49:52.789 --> 49:57.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICK PHILLIPS: I am concerned
that access
to this medication will go away
for many,

49:57.828 --> 49:59.629 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
many people.

49:59.663 --> 50:03.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: Dr. Lee says it's
all part of
a potential change in the way
doctors approach

50:03.467 --> 50:04.434 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
cancer treatment.

50:04.468 --> 50:06.303 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

50:06.336 --> 50:11.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KELVIN LEE: There is an idea
that's developing
of converting cancer into a
chronic disease.

50:11.174 --> 50:16.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We give you a pill that you take
every day,
and it allows you to live a
perfectly normal

50:16.413 --> 50:17.948 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
life.

50:17.981 --> 50:22.619 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: Outside Cuba and
the U.S., there's
great interest in CimaVax.

50:22.652 --> 50:25.155 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's approved in five different
countries.

50:25.188 --> 50:31.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Worldwide, 5,000 patients have
been treated
with the drug since 2011, 1,000
of them Cubans.

50:31.461 --> 50:34.765 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But no one sees CimaVax as a
magic pill.

50:34.798 --> 50:39.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Twenty percent of vaccinated
patients have
not lived longer than the
average survival

50:39.136 --> 50:40.904 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the unvaccinated group.

50:40.937 --> 50:45.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Phillips' doctor, Tim Goggins,
says there
are many unknowns about the
drug.

50:45.075 --> 50:46.810 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

50:46.843 --> 50:50.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIMOTHY GOGGINS: At some point
in time, the
immune system will probably not
respond to

50:50.380 --> 50:52.049 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that cancer cell.

50:52.082 --> 50:54.084 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The cancer cells find a way
around it.

50:54.117 --> 50:58.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: Mick Phillips hopes
the new American
president will allow the
progress he credits

50:58.522 --> 51:00.424 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to Cuban drugs to continue.

51:00.457 --> 51:07.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK PHILLIPS: The key is that
the political
relations staying in place.

51:07.364 --> 51:13.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If that relation stays as it
should, I believe
that we can all benefit from it.

51:13.403 --> 51:17.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY GUTTMAN: Since taking
office, President
Trump has not said much more
about his approach

51:17.641 --> 51:19.076 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
toward Cuba.

51:19.109 --> 51:22.546 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's still unclear what this
could mean for
future trials of the drug.

51:22.579 --> 51:29.286 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Amy
Guttman reporting
from Havana.

51:29.319 --> 51:39.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As we reported at
the top of
tonight's "NewsHour," President
Trump abruptly

51:39.629 --> 51:45.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fired FBI Director James Comey
this evening
over his handling of the
investigation into

51:45.402 --> 51:47.404 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Hillary Clinton's e-mails.

51:47.437 --> 51:51.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president said in a letter
to Comey it
is -- quote -- "essential that
we find new

51:51.741 --> 51:57.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
leadership for the FBI that
restores public
trust and confidence in its
vital law enforcement

51:57.814 --> 51:59.449 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
mission."

51:59.483 --> 52:02.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Moments ago, Republican Senator
John McCain
of Arizona weighed in on the
firing.

52:02.619 --> 52:04.387 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

52:04.421 --> 52:05.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN MCCAIN (R), Arizona: I
regret that the
action had to be taken, and it's
unfortunate,

52:05.755 --> 52:06.690 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
because I think he's a good man.

52:06.723 --> 52:08.492 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The president does have that
authority.

52:08.525 --> 52:12.662 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have always believed that we
should have
a select committee to -- or a
commission,

52:12.696 --> 52:23.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because it's a very large issue
that's gotten
larger, and it will get more
large as time

52:23.073 --> 52:24.808 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
goes by.

52:24.841 --> 52:28.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The number two
Democrat in
the Senate, Dick Durbin of
Illinois, also

52:28.845 --> 52:34.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
questioned whether the FBI's
investigation
into Russian interference in the
last presidential

52:34.384 --> 52:37.220 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
campaign would continue without
Comey.

52:37.254 --> 52:39.122 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

52:39.156 --> 52:43.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD DURBIN (D-IL), Minority
Whip: Any
attempt to stop or undermine
this FBI investigation

52:43.560 --> 52:46.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
would raise grave constitutional
issues.

52:46.863 --> 52:52.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We await clarification by the
White House
as soon as possible as to
whether this investigation

52:52.169 --> 52:56.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will continue and whether it
will have a credible
lead, so that we know that it
will have a

52:56.973 --> 52:58.775 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
just outcome.

52:58.808 --> 53:02.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also tonight,
Democratic Senator
Patrick Leahy called the firing
-- and I'm

53:02.112 --> 53:04.981 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
quoting -- "nothing less than
Nixonian."

53:05.015 --> 53:09.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And late today, the Reuters news
service also
reported that U.S. intelligence
agencies were

53:09.819 --> 53:13.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
given no advanced notice about
